    Date: Mon, 4 Aug 86 19:19:42 PDT
    From: fair@ucbarpa.berkeley.edu (Erik E. Fair)

    I believe that the English use left rooted domain names on their
    network, and they let ucl-cs translate back &amp; forth between their style
    and ours. For some reason, they were terrified of the prospect that the
    host that I use here might remove its `ucb' prefix, as all the other
    hosts at berkeley have done (save for ucbvax). This would give us
    `arpa.berkeley.edu' and give the English terrible headaches...

A nit about your terminology, and it may be important to be precise to
avoid confusion.  The English are &gt;implicitly&lt; rooted on the left.  From
the messages I've gotten from individuals relaying discussions on this
list before I joined, it appears several people now believe &gt;explicit&lt;
rooting to be worthy of consideration.

